description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic Optometrist with paediatric interest to join the Orthoptic team/ Hospital Eye Service at Blackpool Teaching Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust, based at Blackpool Victoria Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be required to work in an Outpatient setting with the Orthoptists. The Orthoptic department consists of 8 Orthoptists, 4 Optometrists and 4 Technicians/ vision screeners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The trust employs 8 Consultant Ophthalmologists, including one Consultant specialising in Paediatric Ophthalmology and Adult Ocular Motility.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post-holder will deliver a paediatric clinic supported by the Orthoptists and ophthalmologists. There may be opportunities to develop the role into other areas of Ophthalmology with consultant support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The department contributes to teaching and clinical audit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications are welcomed from Optometrists who are seeking a position in a friendly and progressive department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hours: 7.5 per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Start date: 4/1/2021&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For informal enquiries about the post please contact Cath Gray Orthoptic Services Manager at catherine.gray1@.nhs.uk or Conrad.beacham@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
